OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1773668263
OL,3,CFormer MP Phil Woolas dies aged 66,
OL,4,Cfamily announce
OL,6,FFormer MP Phil Woolas, who served in
OL,7,Fboth the governments of Tony Blair and
OL,8,FGordon Brown, has died at the age of
OL,9,F66 from brain cancer, his family and
OL,10,Fclose friends have announced.
OL,12,FPhil Woolas, a Labour former minister
OL,13,Fand MP, has died at the age of 66, his
OL,14,Ffamily and close friends have
OL,15,Fannounced.
OL,17,FMr Woolas, who died in the early hours
OL,18,Fof Saturday, served as a minister in
OL,19,Fboth the Blair and Brown governments,
OL,20,Fand as MP for Oldham East and
OL,21,FSaddleworth between 1997 and 2010.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/5
