PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1773668263
OL,3,CFormer MP Phil Woolas dies aged 66,
OL,4,Cfamily announce
OL,6,FA statement attributed to his family
OL,7,Fand close friends announcing his death
OL,8,Fsaid he had "battled the brain cancer,
OL,9,Fglioblastoma".
OL,11,FIt said: "Phil Woolas, former Labour
OL,12,FMP and minister, has died aged 66.
OL,14,F"For more than a year he battled the
OL,15,Fbrain cancer, glioblastoma. He leaves
OL,16,Fhis wife Tracey, his sons Josh and Jed
OL,17,Fand a new grandson, and many friends
OL,18,Fand former colleagues who will all
OL,19,Fmiss him greatly.
OL,26,@pD@MOUqD@MO]sD@JOUvD@AOU
